gw.pl.util.internal

Interface DependenciesLockPolicy


  • public interface DependenciesLockPolicy
    Controls the policy on changing dependencies. The policy is established by the first caller of DependenciesBase.setLockPolicy(DependenciesLockPolicy), and cannot be changed afterwards.
    Author:
    pdalbora

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isLocked()
      Indicates whether dependencies are locked.

    • Method Detail

      • isLocked

        boolean isLocked()
        Indicates whether dependencies are locked. Called on any call to DependenciesBase.setDependency(Class, Object) or DependenciesBase.clearDependencies(). If it returns true, then the call fails with a IllegalStateException.
